\(\cfrac{I_{2}}{I_{1}}=\cfrac{\tan \theta_{2}}{\tan \theta_{1}} \Rightarrow I_{2}=2\left(\cfrac{\tan 60^{\circ}}{\tan 30^{\circ}}\right)\)
\(\therefore I_{2}=6 \mathrm{Amp}\)

quest_title: A car is moving along a straight road with a uniform acceleration. It passes through two points P and Q with velocities 30 km/hr and 40 km/hr respectively. The velocity of car at mid way between P and Q is
explanation_txt:
\(\begin{array}{l}{\mathrm{u}=30 \mathrm{km} / \mathrm{hr} \quad v=40 \mathrm{km} / \mathrm{hr}} \\ {\quad \mathrm{V}^{2}=\mathrm{u}^{2}+2 \mathrm{a} \mathrm{s}} \\ {\text { or, } \mathrm{a}=\cfrac{v^{2}-\mathrm{u}^{2}}{2 \mathrm{s}}} \\ {\quad=\cfrac{40^{2}-30^{2}}{2 \mathrm{s}}}\end{array}\)

For mid point

\(\begin{aligned} \mathrm{V}^{\prime} &=\mathrm{u}^{2}+2 \mathrm{a} \cfrac{\mathrm{s}}{2} \\ &=\mathrm{u}^{2}+\cfrac{\left(40^{2}-30^{2}\right)}{2 \mathrm{s}} \times \mathrm{s} \\ &=30^{2}+\cfrac{\left(40^{2}-30^{2}\right)}{2 \mathrm{s}} \\ &=900+\cfrac{700}{2} \\ &=\cfrac{2500}{2} \end{aligned}\)

\(\therefore \quad V^{1}=\cfrac{50}{\sqrt{2}}=25 \sqrt{2} \mathrm{km} / \mathrm{hr}\)

OR

\(v^{\prime}=\sqrt{\cfrac{u^{2}+v^{2}}{2}}=\sqrt{\cfrac{30^{2}+40^{2}}{2}}\)

\(=25 \sqrt{2} \mathrm{km} / \mathrm{hr}\)
